1
00:00:05,629 --> 00:00:08,397
♪

2
00:01:06,023 --> 00:01:07,656
[SEAGULLS CAWING]

3
00:01:09,059 --> 00:01:11,171
[CROWD CHATTERING]

4
00:01:11,195 --> 00:01:13,040
MAN: My name's on the list. MAN 2: Let us in.

5
00:01:13,064 --> 00:01:14,891
MAN 3: I'll pay you double. WOMAN: Triple!

6
00:01:14,915 --> 00:01:16,031
Behind the ropes, people.

7
00:01:17,334 --> 00:01:19,918
We have special tickets.

8
00:01:24,325 --> 00:01:27,971
Hey! But I just gave you $100.

9
00:01:27,995 --> 00:01:30,357
Thank you. Now get behind the rope.

10
00:01:30,381 --> 00:01:32,542
MAN 4: Serves him right.

11
00:01:32,566 --> 00:01:33,977
WOMAN: Some people think

12
00:01:34,001 --> 00:01:36,329
they can buy anyone.

13
00:01:36,353 --> 00:01:37,664
What do you think?

14
00:01:37,688 --> 00:01:41,223
Uh, well, I, uh... Oh, my.

15
00:01:42,276 --> 00:01:43,926
I don't have a ticket.

16
00:01:45,629 --> 00:01:47,591
Always room for one more.

17
00:01:47,615 --> 00:01:49,526
Thanks, skipper.

18
00:01:49,550 --> 00:01:50,849
Mwah.

19
00:01:56,674 --> 00:01:59,352
Hey, what's she got that I haven't got?

20
00:01:59,376 --> 00:02:00,992
Everything.

21
00:02:02,145 --> 00:02:04,379
[PIANO PLAYING PLEASANT MUSIC]

22
00:02:07,485 --> 00:02:10,029
So, what do you think this stuff's worth, Clark?

23
00:02:10,053 --> 00:02:12,532
To the right collector? Millions.

24
00:02:12,556 --> 00:02:14,985
And my mom made me throw out all my models.

25
00:02:15,009 --> 00:02:16,941
[PEOPLE CHATTERING]

26
00:02:22,332 --> 00:02:25,195
Now, there's a camera-friendly face.

27
00:02:25,219 --> 00:02:27,130
Not exactly newsworthy, Jim.

28
00:02:27,154 --> 00:02:30,155
This is for my private collection.

29
00:02:35,278 --> 00:02:37,979
I hope you got my good side.

30
00:02:39,150 --> 00:02:41,451
Uh... [CHUCKLES]

31
00:02:59,320 --> 00:03:03,205
Ladies and gentlemen, the regatta is about to begin.

32
00:03:07,727 --> 00:03:08,705
[SQUEALS]

33
00:03:08,729 --> 00:03:09,995
Out already?

34
00:03:12,700 --> 00:03:14,516
Jeez.

35
00:03:15,619 --> 00:03:17,352
♪

36
00:03:28,999 --> 00:03:31,044
Fire! Hey!

37
00:03:31,068 --> 00:03:32,467
Somebody get some help!

38
00:03:33,170 --> 00:03:34,553
[CROWD SCREAMING]

39
00:03:37,008 --> 00:03:38,957
Come on, Jimmy. Time to go.

40
00:03:40,477 --> 00:03:42,244
[COUGHING]

41
00:03:43,547 --> 00:03:45,658
Clark! Clark!

42
00:03:45,682 --> 00:03:47,782
Where are you?

43
00:03:49,603 --> 00:03:51,436
♪

44
00:03:57,645 --> 00:03:59,161
[GASPING]

45
00:04:00,263 --> 00:04:01,830
Let's go.

46
00:04:15,212 --> 00:04:16,662
Don't move. I'll get you.

47
00:04:57,838 --> 00:04:59,470
[CINDERS CRACKLING]

48
00:05:02,509 --> 00:05:03,887
Gone.

49
00:05:03,911 --> 00:05:05,810
Like a puff of smoke.

50
00:05:13,737 --> 00:05:15,465
MAN: Move away from the building, sir.

51
00:05:15,489 --> 00:05:17,200
I'm a reporter. I was just...

52
00:05:17,224 --> 00:05:19,319
Sorry. My crew's cleaning hazardous chemicals

53
00:05:19,343 --> 00:05:20,820
from the interior.

54
00:05:20,844 --> 00:05:21,988
You'll have to move back.

55
00:05:22,012 --> 00:05:24,324
Hazardous chemicals?

56
00:05:24,348 --> 00:05:25,691
At a yacht club?

57
00:05:25,715 --> 00:05:27,860
Fuel storage. Petroleum, you know.

58
00:05:27,884 --> 00:05:31,097
The Metropolis Yacht Club is sail-power only.

59
00:05:31,121 --> 00:05:33,115
There's no fuel being stored there.

60
00:05:33,139 --> 00:05:34,384
I wanna see what's going on.

61
00:05:34,408 --> 00:05:36,336
For your own safety...

62
00:05:36,360 --> 00:05:37,759
I suggest you back off.

63
00:05:39,130 --> 00:05:40,746
♪

64
00:06:59,776 --> 00:07:01,142
Keisha, get me Kurt.

65
00:07:07,885 --> 00:07:10,085
My tax dollars at work.

66
00:07:11,738 --> 00:07:14,300
You're going to love the merchandise, Donny.

67
00:07:14,324 --> 00:07:16,436
And I'm offering it to you first

68
00:07:16,460 --> 00:07:19,656
'cause you're my absolute favorite fence.

69
00:07:19,680 --> 00:07:22,926
DONNY: <i>Newspaper said a bunch of boat stuff was missing.</i>

70
00:07:22,950 --> 00:07:25,678
Please. Nautical memorabilia.

71
00:07:25,702 --> 00:07:28,281
Whatever it is, I'm gonna have to pass.

72
00:07:28,305 --> 00:07:29,933
Really?

73
00:07:29,957 --> 00:07:31,334
[BLOWS WHISTLE]

74
00:07:31,358 --> 00:07:34,036
The whistle was touched by the president's lips.

75
00:07:34,060 --> 00:07:35,472
What wasn't?

76
00:07:35,496 --> 00:07:39,292
Uh... Donny, I can give you a really good price.

77
00:07:39,316 --> 00:07:40,644
I have to get out of town.

78
00:07:40,668 --> 00:07:42,812
Look, Volcana, honey, I'd love to help you,

79
00:07:42,836 --> 00:07:44,330
but I can't move that kind of stuff.

80
00:07:44,354 --> 00:07:45,720
Don't you have anything else?

81
00:07:50,143 --> 00:07:51,554
I might.

82
00:07:51,578 --> 00:07:53,289
Yeah? When?

83
00:07:53,313 --> 00:07:56,042
Tuesday. Meet me at the usual place.

84
00:07:56,066 --> 00:07:57,215
You won't be sorry.

85
00:07:59,586 --> 00:08:00,579
[GASPS]

86
00:08:00,603 --> 00:08:03,405
♪

87
00:08:05,692 --> 00:08:09,961
Where exactly is "the usual place"?

88
00:08:10,831 --> 00:08:12,764
♪

89
00:08:16,093 --> 00:08:18,094
[WOMAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY OVER P.A.]

90
00:08:20,966 --> 00:08:23,677
We opened the institute about 20 years ago.

91
00:08:23,701 --> 00:08:25,997
It was the first school to offer paranormal children

92
00:08:26,021 --> 00:08:27,648
a place where they could fit in.

93
00:08:27,672 --> 00:08:30,573
And you also help them develop their abilities?

94
00:08:31,843 --> 00:08:32,992
Let me show you.

95
00:08:48,175 --> 00:08:49,353
Like most things,

96
00:08:49,377 --> 00:08:52,222
telekinesis takes practice.

97
00:08:52,246 --> 00:08:54,809
This little girl had a 40-percent accuracy rating

98
00:08:54,833 --> 00:08:56,215
when she got here.

99
00:09:02,974 --> 00:09:05,157
Now it's up to 92.

100
00:09:06,878 --> 00:09:08,406
Impressive.

101
00:09:08,430 --> 00:09:09,578
But tell me something.

102
00:09:10,298 --> 00:09:11,576
Who pays for all this?

103
00:09:11,600 --> 00:09:13,911
I... I thought you were doing a story

104
00:09:13,935 --> 00:09:15,329
about paranormals.

105
00:09:15,353 --> 00:09:16,931
Just trying to be thorough.

106
00:09:16,955 --> 00:09:18,449
Where does your funding come from?

107
00:09:18,473 --> 00:09:22,704
Why, we have donors and... The government?

108
00:09:22,728 --> 00:09:24,321
[SIGHS]

109
00:09:24,345 --> 00:09:28,308
Mr. Kent, we do some very worthwhile work here,

110
00:09:28,332 --> 00:09:32,296
and the government gives us considerable... encouragement.

111
00:09:32,320 --> 00:09:34,631
But if the public at large knew

112
00:09:34,655 --> 00:09:37,018
that this was how some of their taxes were being spent...

113
00:09:37,042 --> 00:09:38,419
They wouldn't understand.

114
00:09:38,443 --> 00:09:40,709
Exactly.

115
00:09:55,726 --> 00:09:58,577
Keep working, Billy. It'll come.

116
00:10:00,565 --> 00:10:04,328
Ever have anyone who exhibited pyrokinetic abilities?

117
00:10:04,352 --> 00:10:06,080
Py... Pyrokinesis?

118
00:10:06,104 --> 00:10:08,804
You know, the ability to start and control fires.

119
00:10:10,876 --> 00:10:13,554
Oh, dear. Look at the time.

120
00:10:13,578 --> 00:10:16,223
You haven't answered my question.

121
00:10:16,247 --> 00:10:20,150
I have another appointment. Billy will show you out.

122
00:10:22,570 --> 00:10:24,137
I knew he was gonna do that.

123
00:10:27,191 --> 00:10:29,041
MAN: Now, that went well.

124
00:10:30,078 --> 00:10:31,773
I'm doing the best I can.

125
00:10:31,797 --> 00:10:33,379
<i>That's what we're afraid of.</i>

126
00:10:39,937 --> 00:10:41,815
Wh...? Where are you taking me?

127
00:10:41,839 --> 00:10:44,151
A safe house. For your own protection.

128
00:10:44,175 --> 00:10:46,219
Protection? Protection from whom?

129
00:10:46,243 --> 00:10:47,421
Just get in the car.

130
00:10:47,445 --> 00:10:49,278
♪

131
00:10:49,797 --> 00:10:50,958
[GUNSHOT]

132
00:10:50,982 --> 00:10:51,993
Hey!

133
00:10:52,017 --> 00:10:53,427
[GUNSHOT]

134
00:10:53,451 --> 00:10:55,217
Get down!

135
00:10:56,587 --> 00:10:58,304
You see anyone?

136
00:11:03,411 --> 00:11:04,677
[GRUNTS]

137
00:11:05,914 --> 00:11:07,513
Please, don't turn me in.

138
00:11:08,732 --> 00:11:11,017
You gonna tell me what's going on?

139
00:11:13,120 --> 00:11:15,867
You take me some place safe, and I'll tell you everything.

140
00:11:15,891 --> 00:11:17,456
Deal.

141
00:11:21,212 --> 00:11:23,224
By the way, that was a nice diversion tactic.

142
00:11:23,248 --> 00:11:24,558
How'd you do it?

143
00:11:24,582 --> 00:11:26,978
Uh, the tires?

144
00:11:27,002 --> 00:11:29,096
A form of kinetic manipulation.

145
00:11:29,120 --> 00:11:32,672
As they say, "I'm also a client."

146
00:11:34,359 --> 00:11:36,086
[SLURPING]

147
00:11:36,110 --> 00:11:37,755
It was about 10 years ago.

148
00:11:37,779 --> 00:11:40,541
A teenaged girl named Claire Selton came to us

149
00:11:40,565 --> 00:11:42,927
with enormous pyrokinetic potential.

150
00:11:42,951 --> 00:11:44,645
But I never got to see her fulfill it.

151
00:11:44,669 --> 00:11:45,763
Why not?

152
00:11:45,787 --> 00:11:48,266
The government men. They took her.

153
00:11:48,290 --> 00:11:49,533
Took her?

154
00:11:49,557 --> 00:11:50,685
As in, kidnapped?

155
00:11:50,709 --> 00:11:53,220
Mm-hm. Can I have another?

156
00:11:53,244 --> 00:11:54,605
What did they do with her?

157
00:11:54,629 --> 00:11:58,242
Stripped away her past, code-named her "Volcana,"

158
00:11:58,266 --> 00:11:59,409
and tried their hardest

159
00:11:59,433 --> 00:12:01,062
to turn her into a living weapon.

160
00:12:01,086 --> 00:12:02,763
Poor kid.

161
00:12:02,787 --> 00:12:04,882
Ah, don't feel too sorry for her.

162
00:12:04,906 --> 00:12:07,001
If this is the same person we're talking about,

163
00:12:07,025 --> 00:12:09,587
she could give as good as she got.

164
00:12:09,611 --> 00:12:10,788
[SLURPING]

165
00:12:10,812 --> 00:12:12,722
Ahhh.

166
00:12:12,746 --> 00:12:15,276
This is almost paranormally good.

167
00:12:15,300 --> 00:12:16,632
[LAUGHS]

168
00:12:17,935 --> 00:12:20,631
I... Paranormal. That's... That's really good.

169
00:12:20,655 --> 00:12:23,022
♪

170
00:12:25,293 --> 00:12:27,488
Uh, I have an errand I need to run.

171
00:12:27,512 --> 00:12:29,740
Oh, don't worry about me.

172
00:12:29,764 --> 00:12:31,175
[SLURPING]

173
00:12:31,199 --> 00:12:33,627
I'll be fine.

174
00:12:33,651 --> 00:12:35,217
[BURPS]

175
00:12:38,405 --> 00:12:43,042
Life, liberty and the pursuit of my happiness.

176
00:12:50,902 --> 00:12:53,130
You're gonna make me earn this, aren't you?

177
00:12:53,154 --> 00:12:55,432
Don't do it, Volcana.

178
00:12:55,456 --> 00:12:56,883
I can help you.

179
00:12:56,907 --> 00:12:58,168
No, thanks.

180
00:12:58,192 --> 00:13:00,203
These days, I help myself.

181
00:13:00,227 --> 00:13:03,273
Listen, nobody will blame you for what you've done.

182
00:13:03,297 --> 00:13:05,776
But the stealing has to stop. Now.

183
00:13:05,800 --> 00:13:09,129
Stop? I'm just getting warmed up.

184
00:13:09,153 --> 00:13:10,330
Aah!

185
00:13:10,354 --> 00:13:13,089
♪

186
00:13:14,708 --> 00:13:15,669
[GASPS]

187
00:13:15,693 --> 00:13:18,606
You have to trust me, Volcana.

188
00:13:18,630 --> 00:13:20,641
Do you know how many times I've heard that?

189
00:13:20,665 --> 00:13:21,942
From my parents

190
00:13:21,966 --> 00:13:24,028
before they shuffled me off to the institute?

191
00:13:24,052 --> 00:13:26,864
From the institute just before they turned me over to the feds.

192
00:13:26,888 --> 00:13:28,348
And from the government

193
00:13:28,372 --> 00:13:31,007
just before they took away my life!

194
00:13:38,849 --> 00:13:41,401
And that was with my left hand.

195
00:13:45,222 --> 00:13:46,572
[PEOPLE SCREAMING]

196
00:13:52,580 --> 00:13:54,297
♪

197
00:14:08,046 --> 00:14:10,507
Look. Amazing.

198
00:14:10,531 --> 00:14:11,851
WOMAN: What was that?

199
00:14:13,918 --> 00:14:16,096
Donny, I've got something for you.

200
00:14:16,120 --> 00:14:19,288
It wasn't what I originally hoped for but...

201
00:14:25,996 --> 00:14:28,592
I guess I always knew you'd catch up to me, Kurt.

202
00:14:28,616 --> 00:14:32,646
Now leave, before I make it even hotter for you.

203
00:14:32,670 --> 00:14:34,815
You've been bad, Volcana.

204
00:14:34,839 --> 00:14:36,783
You've been worse.

205
00:14:36,807 --> 00:14:39,887
And now that we've recapped the past two years...

206
00:14:39,911 --> 00:14:41,555
You shouldn't have left us.

207
00:14:41,579 --> 00:14:43,173
I don't like being used.

208
00:14:43,197 --> 00:14:44,958
All for a good cause.

209
00:14:44,982 --> 00:14:46,777
I'll be the judge of that.

210
00:14:46,801 --> 00:14:50,130
And if you're thinking you can make me go back, forget it.

211
00:14:50,154 --> 00:14:52,966
Now, that's where you're wrong.

212
00:14:52,990 --> 00:14:55,753
♪

213
00:14:55,777 --> 00:14:57,210
Aah!

214
00:15:04,185 --> 00:15:07,915
You see, we've had two years to think about... how to do it.

215
00:15:07,939 --> 00:15:10,223
♪

216
00:15:14,285 --> 00:15:16,497
[HORNS HONKING IN DISTANCE]

217
00:15:16,521 --> 00:15:19,666
So I see cop cars outside this hotel.

218
00:15:19,690 --> 00:15:22,202
Desk clerk tells me she heard some kind of struggle

219
00:15:22,226 --> 00:15:24,220
in a room she rented to a redhead.

220
00:15:24,244 --> 00:15:25,673
You call that a story?

221
00:15:25,697 --> 00:15:27,174
Here's the weird part:

222
00:15:27,198 --> 00:15:29,743
The room was covered in foam.

223
00:15:29,767 --> 00:15:31,979
The police say it's a powerful fire retardant,

224
00:15:32,003 --> 00:15:34,347
but get this: There was no fire.

225
00:15:34,371 --> 00:15:35,766
Oh, now, that's a headline.

226
00:15:35,790 --> 00:15:38,557
LOIS: "No Fire in Hotel Room."

227
00:15:44,916 --> 00:15:47,649
♪

228
00:15:55,026 --> 00:15:57,488
Shred 'em. And then we're outta here.

229
00:15:57,512 --> 00:15:58,822
Hey! Hey!

230
00:15:58,846 --> 00:16:00,607
Where did they take her?

231
00:16:00,631 --> 00:16:01,975
[ENERGY SURGING]

232
00:16:01,999 --> 00:16:04,427
It's a G-40 blue laser, alien.

233
00:16:04,451 --> 00:16:05,728
One shot can penetrate

234
00:16:05,752 --> 00:16:08,164
five feet of tempered steel in 0.3 seconds.

235
00:16:08,188 --> 00:16:11,457
I don't think even... Argh!

236
00:16:17,264 --> 00:16:18,424
I repeat:

237
00:16:18,448 --> 00:16:20,326
Where did they take her?

238
00:16:20,350 --> 00:16:21,500
[WHIMPERING]

239
00:16:38,019 --> 00:16:39,985
♪

240
00:16:43,941 --> 00:16:45,586
KURT: No escape, Volcana.

241
00:16:45,610 --> 00:16:48,254
The tank is filled with an inert gas.

242
00:16:48,278 --> 00:16:50,791
The breathing mask is your only source of oxygen.

243
00:16:50,815 --> 00:16:53,093
Not enough for you to start a fire.

244
00:16:53,117 --> 00:16:55,050
And should you try...

245
00:16:57,671 --> 00:16:59,149
[COUGHING]

246
00:16:59,173 --> 00:17:02,569
I wouldn't give us any trouble. Understood?

247
00:17:02,593 --> 00:17:04,387
<i>[PANTING OVER SPEAKER]</i>

248
00:17:04,411 --> 00:17:06,540
<i>Okay, you win.</i>

249
00:17:06,564 --> 00:17:08,859
<i>Who do you want me to kill?</i>

250
00:17:08,883 --> 00:17:10,026
My dear, you can't believe

251
00:17:10,050 --> 00:17:12,146
we'd trust you with another assignment.

252
00:17:12,170 --> 00:17:14,681
However, it did cost us a lot of money

253
00:17:14,705 --> 00:17:16,066
to develop your talents,

254
00:17:16,090 --> 00:17:17,967
and we'd like to get some of it back.

255
00:17:17,991 --> 00:17:19,052
<i>How?</i>

256
00:17:19,076 --> 00:17:20,337
A foreign government

257
00:17:20,361 --> 00:17:22,522
doing metagenetic experiments wants to study you.

258
00:17:22,546 --> 00:17:24,224
<i>You mean dissect me.</i>

259
00:17:24,248 --> 00:17:26,225
Probably. When they're done playing.

260
00:17:26,249 --> 00:17:27,716
[WHIRRING]

261
00:17:31,389 --> 00:17:32,716
Superman.

262
00:17:32,740 --> 00:17:35,535
Just in time.

263
00:17:35,559 --> 00:17:37,192
[GUNS COCKING]

264
00:17:38,613 --> 00:17:39,840
Really?

265
00:17:39,864 --> 00:17:41,741
You can see we've shut down Volcana.

266
00:17:41,765 --> 00:17:43,510
As you know, she's a real loose cannon.

267
00:17:43,534 --> 00:17:45,379
You're the loose cannon.

268
00:17:45,403 --> 00:17:47,014
You and your entire operation.

269
00:17:47,038 --> 00:17:49,415
Your friends told me Project Firestorm's funding

270
00:17:49,439 --> 00:17:50,767
was cut off years ago.

271
00:17:50,791 --> 00:17:54,070
This isn't the government. It's just you.

272
00:17:54,094 --> 00:17:56,378
♪

273
00:18:23,707 --> 00:18:24,973
<i>Yes.</i>

274
00:18:30,347 --> 00:18:32,592
MAN: Move it! Move it!

275
00:18:32,616 --> 00:18:34,616
[ALL YELLING]

276
00:18:43,527 --> 00:18:45,372
Thanks.

277
00:18:45,396 --> 00:18:48,163
Don't get sentimental. It's a one-time thing.

278
00:18:54,322 --> 00:18:56,504
♪

279
00:19:01,612 --> 00:19:02,927
[GASPS]

280
00:19:10,387 --> 00:19:13,483
Shoe's on the other foot, eh, lover?

281
00:19:13,507 --> 00:19:15,652
Volcana, please.

282
00:19:15,676 --> 00:19:17,104
SUPERMAN: Volcana, no.

283
00:19:17,128 --> 00:19:18,772
Let the courts deal with him.

284
00:19:18,796 --> 00:19:21,441
You'll understand if I'm a little skeptical

285
00:19:21,465 --> 00:19:23,527
about the justice system.

286
00:19:23,551 --> 00:19:25,279
[GASPS]

287
00:19:25,303 --> 00:19:27,769
I prefer my own justice.

288
00:19:31,875 --> 00:19:34,026
And if you're not part of my solution...

289
00:19:36,129 --> 00:19:38,147
you're part of my problem.

290
00:19:39,450 --> 00:19:40,698
No!

291
00:20:02,840 --> 00:20:05,985
Hey, I told you last time. I like chunky.

292
00:20:06,009 --> 00:20:07,170
Adapt.

293
00:20:07,194 --> 00:20:11,107
Food, shelter, sunshine... Could be worse.

294
00:20:11,131 --> 00:20:12,893
Could be Metropolis Women's Prison

295
00:20:12,917 --> 00:20:14,677
if you weren't so volatile.

296
00:20:14,701 --> 00:20:17,396
Polite to the end. Your mother raised you well.

297
00:20:17,420 --> 00:20:18,682
I was lucky.

298
00:20:18,706 --> 00:20:20,450
Yes, you were.

299
00:20:20,474 --> 00:20:22,185
I hope you'll think of me.

300
00:20:22,209 --> 00:20:25,639
Especially on those cold Metropolis nights.

301
00:20:25,663 --> 00:20:27,307
Don't you ever cool down?

302
00:20:27,331 --> 00:20:29,130
No.

303
00:20:41,778 --> 00:20:45,313
♪

